  ZendeskAdapter, SatwsAdapter, TokenizationAdapter — each owns its Router cases internally and exposes a domain-language interface. Feature code calls zendeskAdapter.widgetJWT(), not a raw Router case with a vendor URL. Vendor changes become
   a one-file problem.                                                                                                                                                                                                                            
   
  7. Consider co-locating Router enums with their feature modules.                                                                                                                                                                                
  With 12 domains and 70+ endpoints, a centralized Router monolith is hard to navigate and creates merge contention. Each domain module owns its Router enum. ClaraNetworking provides the protocol and the performer; domains own their
  definitions. This aligns with the package-by-feature principle already in the playbook. 


